sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Reata Pharmaceuticals Inc (Symbol: RETA), where a total volume of 1,585 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 158,500 underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 49.2% of RETA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 321,970 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $240 strike call option expiring January 17, 2020, with 1,216 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 121,600 underlying shares of RETA.
